Today is The Cutting Edge Barbershops 18 year Anniversary! As I reflect over the course of the last 18 years, I wanted to offer new business owners words of encouragement and advice

	1.	If you open a business, make sure you LOVE what you do.! When you stop loving it, it’s time sell.
	2.	Don’t open a business for money. If you find something you love the money will find you.
	3.	Never stop running your business. You must  continue to evolve every year in order to have THE CUTTING EDGE ✂️. 
	4.	Do something in your business that the competition is not doing. Find your own lane.
	5.	Hire chemistry rather than talent. This has always helped me win. Don’t just hire to fill a void, it never works out. 
	6.	Never stop learning… what ever business you have make sure to invest in yourself and your business. Contniue your education, take classes, network with people in your field. Find a Mentor!
	7.	The day you open your business is the day you need to start planing your retirement. How will you exit? Selling your business as its dying won’t get you much but selling at the peak will. Also consider bringing in a partner that can add value and a fresh perspective. 
	8.	Don’t worry about your competitors! Trust me you will have enough to worry about in your own business. If all business’s do what they need to do everyone will eat!
	9.	Last, run a business that you would patronize. If you wouldn’t go why would anyone else? 

Lastly I wanted to show my gratitude and say a special Thank You to my team! You continue to raise the bar and grow as individuals as well as together as a whole. I appreciate all the dedication to the shop!

Big thanks to all of our customers for all the years of support! We are truly grateful for your business! We will continue to strive to offer you the best service and experience that we can!
